    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>St. Thomas</placeName>
                <date>Feby 3. 5608</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isc Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">It is really a long while since that I have<lb/> had this pleasure
                but absence has prevented my attention<lb/> ere this to your various favors; every
                thing is right except<lb/> the pack of Occidents for <date>October</date> which did
                not come by the<lb/> Emily altho' your letter said so, <persName>Captain
                    Davis</persName> says that<lb/> no such pack came on board. I intend to make you
                a<lb/> shipment of Bay Water in a short time, &amp; will see if accounts<lb/> can't
                be squared, I have not sold a single <sic>sett</sic> of Parasah<lb/> or Prayer books
                since my last; I have disposed of 3 Prayer<lb/> Books Oblige me &amp; let me know
                the names of those for<lb/> whom I ordered the Pentateuch. I am not yet paid by
                some<lb/> I write this evening to <persName>James Henry Esq</persName> at
                    <placeName>New York</placeName> for<lb/> Matzot, if they bake early in
                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> (say earlier<lb/> than <placeName>N
                    York</placeName>, the baker can send to him for me 4 Cases<lb/> each 25
                    <add>?</add> Matzot &amp; 2 Setts Shemurim it would be necessary<lb/> to inform
                him of such intention that he does not engage<lb/> any for me, he is limited to
                    <date>24th March</date> to ship</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Wishing you health &amp; success</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">I am Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Your Obedt Servt</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">M B Simmons</persName>
            </p>
            <p><placeName>Charleston</placeName> wants what it will not obtain, such is my idea
                as<lb/> $1000 is not an inducement for such a scholar.</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <addressee>Revd Isc Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">via <placeName>N. York</placeName></p>
            <p rend="The following written on the back of the envelope."/>
            <p>Respt yours &amp; your obt ser.</p>
            <p><persName>Elijah</persName>. Dr <add>?</add></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Wilmington</placeName>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>
                    <hi rend="underline">N.C.</hi>
                </placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
